{
  // HOW TO ADD A NEW LANGUAGE
  // 1. Copy this file to lang/<code>.json (e.g. lang/de.json for German).
  // 2. Translate only the values (the text right of each ":"). Never touch
  //    the keys (the text in quotes on the left), and never remove/rename a
  //    placeholder like {name}, {count}, {pct} — the app fills those in at
  //    runtime. A few values also contain "\n" (newline) — keep it as-is.
  // 3. Update _meta below to your language.
  // 4. Add { "code": "<code>", "label": "🇩🇪 Deutsch" } to the SUPPORTED
  //    array in js/i18n.js so it shows up in the language picker.
  // 5. These "//" comments are stripped before parsing — they're not valid
  //    JSON, so any JSON validator/linter will flag them; that's expected.

